                     ------- sdcv ------------
install sdcv from the official repos; then download dictionaries from https://web.archive.org/web/20200702000038/http://download.huzheng.org/ ; then tar -xjvf then and put them in /usr/share/stardict/dic/; use a wrapper bash function like: function dict() {
    sdcv -n --utf8-output --color "$@" 2>&1 | \
    fold --width=$(tput cols) | \
    less --quit-if-one-screen -RX
}
                    ------ zathura ---------
                    ------ vocage -------
how to export .... Use File > Save a Copy.
Goto the place, where you want to save the file.
Choose the file type Text CSV (.csv) form the drop down list.
Uncheck Automatic file name extension and enter the file name including the correct filename extension. CheckEdit filter settings. Click Save. Now you get a dialog for the settings.
In the drop-down list field delimiter select the item {Tab}.
